race.comment: SEPTIMUS (3) has put together back-to-back placings since the Newcastle Maiden win. He's well placed at country level and is the one they have to beat. DUNWITHYA (1) won his Maiden over a mile and then didn't have the best of it against the above at Kembla Grange. Presents fitter and shapes as the threat. PONTIAC (2) should be assessed on his CL1 win at Canberra two back. Just battled there last time but that was in better grade. He's on a 6-day return and keeps the handy 2kg claim. LANDMARK LADY (7) made good improvement at Moruya over a mile. The indications are that the middle distance will suit.
